1
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:52,160
I was just as scared as you were.

2
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:54,760
I was scared of losing you.

3
00:02:57,560 --> 00:02:58,760
Tell me!

4
00:02:59,880 --> 00:03:01,440
Who threw that woman into the sea?

5
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:06,680
Pong.

6
00:03:07,200 --> 00:03:08,200
Pong.

7
00:03:08,880 --> 00:03:11,400
Mr. Phum, I...

8
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:15,159
I have to find out who that woman is

9
00:03:15,160 --> 00:03:19,320
and why she hates my father so much
that she's trying to kill him.

10
00:04:06,320 --> 00:04:07,400
Mr. Phum.

11
00:04:12,320 --> 00:04:14,679
You don't seem very happy to see me.

12
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:17,279
That's because I'm already used to
this kind of behavior from you.

13
00:04:18,279 --> 00:04:21,440
I know
why you've been hanging around here.

14
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:25,079
Do you want Sarai's land that badly?

15
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:27,480
Are you keeping it as a memorial
to your love or something?

16
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:29,959
After she betrayed you like that,

17
00:04:29,960 --> 00:04:32,479
you're still hung up on her.
You're such a fool.

18
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:34,760
I've been a fool
ever since I made you my wife.

19
00:04:52,840 --> 00:04:54,000
Mr. Phum.

20
00:04:54,840 --> 00:04:55,880
I'm sorry.

21
00:04:57,240 --> 00:04:58,559
I'm sorry.

22
00:04:58,560 --> 00:04:59,959
Let go of me.

23
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:01,999
- I'm sorry.
- I said let go.

24
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,680
No. I'm sorry.

25
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:09,000
Mr. Phum! Mr. Phum!

26
00:05:47,440 --> 00:05:49,039
<i>After she betrayed you like that,</i>

27
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:52,200
<i>you're still hung up on her.
You're such a fool.</i>

28
00:05:55,840 --> 00:05:58,760
Sarai. Sarai.

29
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:01,479
The moment you got home,

30
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:04,800
you came straight to Sarai's room?

31
00:06:12,520 --> 00:06:14,200
You even brought her a gift.

32
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:16,640
Too bad

33
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:18,760
she'll never get a chance to use it.

34
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:21,360
Where's Sarai?

35
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:25,680
I asked where Sarai is.

36
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:29,480
She's gone.

37
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:34,000
You drove her away, didn't you?

38
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:36,879
She ran away with another man.

39
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:38,280
I don't believe you.

40
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:52,880
Sarai. You're disgusting.

41
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:55,080
You shameless woman.

42
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:10,720
Bill, please.

43
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:27,840
You can just send me off here.

44
00:07:30,640 --> 00:07:32,960
There's something I want to ask of you.

45
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:35,400
What is it?

46
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:37,560
I don't want you

47
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:40,320
getting involved in this anymore.

48
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:43,280
- But--
- Well.

49
00:07:44,760 --> 00:07:45,920
I'm worried about you.

50
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:51,560
That woman ghost might hurt you.

51
00:07:53,480 --> 00:07:55,360
I'll handle this myself.

52
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:01,959
I can't promise you that.

53
00:08:01,960 --> 00:08:03,400
Why not?

54
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:06,120
Because I'm worried about you too.

55
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:18,399
We'll investigate this together.

56
00:08:18,400 --> 00:08:19,440
Okay?

57
00:08:22,280 --> 00:08:23,440
Okay.

58
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:31,400
Agreed.

59
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:36,558
But we haven't sealed the deal
with a handshake yet.

60
00:08:36,559 --> 00:08:38,200
Is that really necessary?

61
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:40,440
Of course.

62
00:08:41,400 --> 00:08:43,960
Otherwise, how can it count as a promise?

63
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:04,120
Thank you for worrying about me.

64
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:16,120
Well, I should go inside now.

65
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,160
Okay.

66
00:09:55,640 --> 00:09:57,080
Where have you been?

67
00:10:01,760 --> 00:10:03,600
I've been waiting forever.

68
00:10:08,560 --> 00:10:11,519
What's wrong? Why is your face so red?

69
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:13,040
Are you sick?

70
00:10:14,360 --> 00:10:15,640
No.

71
00:10:17,040 --> 00:10:18,000
What's going on?

72
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:23,239
Oh, that sacred thread.

73
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:24,920
You found it?

74
00:10:26,280 --> 00:10:28,279
I asked the Venerable Sir for another one.

75
00:10:28,280 --> 00:10:31,319
Now I'm not afraid
of that woman ghost anymore.

76
00:10:31,320 --> 00:10:33,599
Mook, call Mr. Phum again.

77
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:36,440
I'm ready to tell him everything.

78
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:41,680
What's wrong?

79
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:46,480
I met Mr. Narathon today.

80
00:10:47,160 --> 00:10:48,880
So I told him everything.

81
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:52,880
I don't see a problem.
They're father and son.

82
00:10:54,480 --> 00:10:58,400
But Mr. Narathon
wants to investigate this himself.

83
00:10:59,280 --> 00:11:02,640
You mean we're not
telling Mr. Phum anymore?

84
00:11:04,680 --> 00:11:06,720
What does Mr. Narathon suspect?

85
00:11:09,240 --> 00:11:10,920
I don't know either.

86
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:26,439
Have some hot cocoa. It's good for stress.

87
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:27,360
Thanks.

88
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:31,560
You've got it bad.

89
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:42,360
Who's showing up this late?

90
00:11:54,760 --> 00:11:55,640
Dad?

91
00:11:58,280 --> 00:11:59,440
He reeks of alcohol.

92
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:04,520
Your dad really went all out.
He actually drank himself unconscious.

93
00:12:06,080 --> 00:12:07,799
As long as I can remember,

94
00:12:07,800 --> 00:12:10,000
I've never seen him this drunk.

95
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:25,000
I don't think
he's sobering up anytime soon.

96
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:30,360
Looks like we'll have to sleep
in the living room tonight.

97
00:12:31,240 --> 00:12:33,960
No problem. I'll go get the bedding ready.

98
00:12:41,880 --> 00:12:42,880
Sarai.

99
00:12:44,400 --> 00:12:45,440
Sarai...

100
00:12:47,560 --> 00:12:49,680
Why did you do this to me?

101
00:12:51,560 --> 00:12:53,480
You shameless woman.

102
00:12:55,760 --> 00:13:00,040
I'll kill you. I'll kill you, Sarai.

103
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:47,160
Why aren't you doing
what I ordered you to?

104
00:13:50,840 --> 00:13:54,040
If you still don't make a move,
I'll hire someone else.

105
00:13:54,920 --> 00:13:56,600
No one will take this job.

106
00:13:57,120 --> 00:13:58,400
Why not?

107
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:02,320
Because the police have sealed off
all of Skull Island now.

108
00:14:02,960 --> 00:14:04,080
Damn it!

109
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,359
This is bad!

110
00:14:06,360 --> 00:14:08,799
How long do I have to wait
before I finally get the treasure?

111
00:14:08,800 --> 00:14:10,360
Calm down.

112
00:14:11,120 --> 00:14:14,920
Once everything quiets down,
the police will leave on their own.

113
00:14:15,560 --> 00:14:16,920
I'll make my move right away.

114
00:14:18,640 --> 00:14:20,200
Hurry up.

115
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:22,560
You're so slow.

116
00:15:18,280 --> 00:15:19,720
It's you!

117
00:15:20,760 --> 00:15:22,800
You still haven't learned your lesson?

118
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:26,399
You still haven't learned?

119
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:28,479
Fine. I'll give you one.

120
00:15:28,480 --> 00:15:30,640
Pong, Pong!

121
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:34,320
What did you say?

122
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:46,360
Do you remember everything now, Sompong?

123
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:47,960
I remember.

124
00:15:50,640 --> 00:15:54,400
You... You're Pong!

125
00:15:55,520 --> 00:15:56,719
What else?

126
00:15:56,720 --> 00:15:58,680
You...

127
00:16:01,280 --> 00:16:04,079
You threw the woman into the sea!

128
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:06,480
She fell into the sea! She fell!

129
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:09,560
And then what?

130
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:12,720
And then...

131
00:16:21,240 --> 00:16:26,360
she floated up and down.

132
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:28,240
She floated away.

133
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:32,439
Floating up...

134
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:34,840
- Bastard. You scared me.
- ...and down...

135
00:16:36,160 --> 00:16:37,880
I thought you remembered
that we killed that...

136
00:16:49,440 --> 00:16:53,400
Pong really threw a woman into the sea?

137
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:55,800
Yes.

138
00:17:07,800 --> 00:17:08,800
Pong.

139
00:17:10,160 --> 00:17:12,319
You must want to know it so much

140
00:17:12,880 --> 00:17:14,800
that you follow me all the way here.

141
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:21,199
Pong, wait. I didn't mean to.

142
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:24,280
I've been suspicious about
what that madman kept saying.

143
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:26,479
I didn't mean to.

144
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:29,799
I swear I won't tell anyone.

145
00:17:29,800 --> 00:17:31,119
I promise.

146
00:17:31,120 --> 00:17:32,959
You know you're like my idol.

147
00:17:32,960 --> 00:17:36,120
I really look up to you.

148
00:17:36,960 --> 00:17:37,879
That much?

149
00:17:37,880 --> 00:17:39,680
Yes.

150
00:17:41,080 --> 00:17:44,080
You know I'm a coward, but you see this?

151
00:17:44,800 --> 00:17:47,759
I endured the pain of getting this
because I wanted to be like you.

152
00:17:47,760 --> 00:17:49,999
I really look up to you.

153
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:53,359
I promise I won't tell anyone.

154
00:17:53,360 --> 00:17:54,960
Please don't hurt me.

155
00:17:55,560 --> 00:17:57,679
I swear

156
00:17:57,680 --> 00:18:00,600
with all my pride. I won't tell anyone.

157
00:18:01,120 --> 00:18:02,040
I really won't.

158
00:18:29,920 --> 00:18:31,160
I'm sorry, Piak.

159
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:41,400
Why, bro?

160
00:18:51,760 --> 00:18:52,840
You...

161
00:18:54,040 --> 00:18:56,640
You killed again.

162
00:19:03,880 --> 00:19:05,800
And I have to kill you too...

163
00:19:09,240 --> 00:19:10,719
before you remember more.

164
00:19:10,720 --> 00:19:11,680
No.

165
00:19:13,920 --> 00:19:15,200
Where are you going?!

166
00:19:46,200 --> 00:19:47,160
Damn it!

167
00:20:19,320 --> 00:20:20,840
I'm sorry

168
00:20:21,800 --> 00:20:23,440
for using your body.

169
00:20:29,880 --> 00:20:31,680
But I have to find out

170
00:20:32,840 --> 00:20:33,960
who it was

171
00:20:35,120 --> 00:20:37,160
who ordered the murder of me

172
00:20:39,880 --> 00:20:41,600
and my child.

173
00:20:50,440 --> 00:20:54,839
May you be blessed with long life,
grace, happiness, and strength.

174
00:20:54,840 --> 00:20:56,360
<i>Sathu.</i>

175
00:20:59,120 --> 00:21:01,239
Where is Cherd today?

176
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:03,159
I usually see him offering alms
with you every day.

177
00:21:03,160 --> 00:21:05,679
Cherd went to help
put out a fire last night.

178
00:21:05,680 --> 00:21:09,280
He got back almost at dawn,
so he couldn't wake up.

179
00:21:10,480 --> 00:21:11,840
Where was the fire?

180
00:21:12,440 --> 00:21:13,960
At that crazy Sompong's hut.

181
00:21:14,560 --> 00:21:17,599
He must have gone mad
and set the hut on fire.

182
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:20,800
He got burned to death in it.
What terrible karma.

183
00:21:23,320 --> 00:21:25,240
I have to go now, Venerable Sir.

184
00:22:04,400 --> 00:22:06,200
Did I really get that drunk?

185
00:22:39,160 --> 00:22:40,280
Thon...

186
00:23:02,560 --> 00:23:04,559
Mr. Phum, you're awake.

187
00:23:04,560 --> 00:23:05,560
Yes.

188
00:23:09,320 --> 00:23:12,560
I knew you and Thon
would probably wear the same size.

189
00:23:15,960 --> 00:23:17,480
You prepared the clothes for me?

190
00:23:18,080 --> 00:23:19,119
Yes.

191
00:23:19,120 --> 00:23:20,159
Where's Thon?

192
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:23,040
Well, he went to the police station.

193
00:23:24,480 --> 00:23:25,919
The police called him in.

194
00:23:25,920 --> 00:23:28,760
They wanted additional questioning
about what happened on Skull Island.

195
00:23:35,880 --> 00:23:37,599
Ms. Kaimook, are you sure

196
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:39,360
you were...

197
00:23:40,840 --> 00:23:42,000
really taken by a ghost?

198
00:23:44,200 --> 00:23:45,319
Officer,

199
00:23:45,320 --> 00:23:48,760
are you saying that my daughter is lying?

200
00:23:49,480 --> 00:23:50,840
Please don't misunderstand me.

201
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:54,279
The reason I asked Ms. Kaimook
to come in for another statement

202
00:23:54,280 --> 00:23:56,719
is because the police
searched the entire island,

203
00:23:56,720 --> 00:23:59,480
but we found nothing unusual.

204
00:24:02,800 --> 00:24:04,159
Officer,

205
00:24:04,160 --> 00:24:09,440
if a ghost doesn't want you
to see it, of course you won't.

206
00:24:15,280 --> 00:24:17,120
Mr. Narathon is here, sir.

207
00:24:17,880 --> 00:24:19,160
- Send him in.
- Yes, sir.

208
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:24,640
Can we leave now?

209
00:24:25,600 --> 00:24:26,480
Yes.

210
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:28,760
Thank you very much for your cooperation.

211
00:24:29,480 --> 00:24:33,000
If anything else comes up,
I may have to trouble you again.

212
00:24:33,760 --> 00:24:38,040
Of course. We're happy
to cooperate fully with the police.

213
00:24:38,640 --> 00:24:39,720
Thank you very much.

214
00:24:40,720 --> 00:24:41,960
Goodbye.

215
00:24:52,240 --> 00:24:53,080
Hello.

216
00:24:54,920 --> 00:24:58,640
If you hadn't gone to intern at SAVE SEA,
you wouldn't have had all this trouble.

217
00:25:00,920 --> 00:25:01,880
Let's go.

218
00:25:07,520 --> 00:25:08,680
We'll be going now.

219
00:25:11,960 --> 00:25:15,040
Well, there's something
I want to talk to you about,

220
00:25:15,560 --> 00:25:17,200
but calling probably isn't convenient.

221
00:25:19,560 --> 00:25:21,199
You can message me.

222
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:22,320
POLICE MAJOR NATTAPONG BOONPHU
INSPECTOR

223
00:25:39,040 --> 00:25:40,400
What are you doing, Mook?

224
00:25:42,040 --> 00:25:45,480
I'm looking for information
about the missing pirate ship.

225
00:25:49,320 --> 00:25:53,120
You're still interested
in that crazy ghost on the island?

226
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:58,160
I want to know who he really was,

227
00:25:58,720 --> 00:26:00,880
and why he died on that island.

228
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:04,400
That's interesting.

229
00:26:06,480 --> 00:26:11,480
Why haven't any of
the relevant authorities looked into it,

230
00:26:12,160 --> 00:26:14,159
even though everyone suspects

231
00:26:14,160 --> 00:26:16,680
it might be connected
to the missing ancient gold?

232
00:26:18,080 --> 00:26:20,479
I think I know now

233
00:26:20,480 --> 00:26:22,520
why the story went quiet.

234
00:26:23,640 --> 00:26:24,640
Why?

235
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:29,200
Because there's no evidence at all.

236
00:26:29,800 --> 00:26:33,480
I've been searching for hours.
There's nothing.

237
00:26:38,360 --> 00:26:41,240
It's like everything was erased.

238
00:26:44,920 --> 00:26:46,200
Who erased it?

239
00:27:17,960 --> 00:27:19,240
RESTRICTED AREA.
STRICTLY NO ENTRY TO THE ISLAND.

240
00:27:50,960 --> 00:27:52,959
MR. NARATHON
I WANT TO SEE YOU.

241
00:27:52,960 --> 00:27:54,839
WHEN?

242
00:27:54,840 --> 00:27:56,879
NOW.

243
00:27:56,880 --> 00:27:58,799
IT'S ALREADY LATE.

244
00:27:58,800 --> 00:27:59,760
IT'S URGENT.

245
00:28:12,800 --> 00:28:15,039
I'LL WAIT AT THE BEACH
IN FRONT OF YOUR HOUSE.

246
00:28:15,040 --> 00:28:18,880
OKAY.

247
00:28:51,960 --> 00:28:53,120
Kaimook.

248
00:28:55,600 --> 00:28:56,760
Venerable Sir?

249
00:28:58,880 --> 00:29:00,640
Go back inside now.

250
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:16,360
Go inside.

251
00:29:19,800 --> 00:29:20,840
Yes.

252
00:29:51,240 --> 00:29:52,160
Hey.

253
00:29:53,200 --> 00:29:54,040
What kind of ship is that?

254
00:29:54,720 --> 00:29:57,280
Is that the ghost ship
everyone talks about?

255
00:29:57,880 --> 00:29:58,880
Oh?

256
00:29:59,680 --> 00:30:01,320
- No.
- I'm scared.

257
00:30:16,800 --> 00:30:18,760
Why are you interfering in my affairs?

258
00:30:20,360 --> 00:30:22,520
Go back to where you belong.

259
00:30:23,560 --> 00:30:26,080
Don't create more karma.

260
00:30:35,360 --> 00:30:37,440
Not your real body?

261
00:31:00,520 --> 00:31:03,680
A man like you has cultivated
the Dhamma to this level?

262
00:31:06,520 --> 00:31:11,520
The past cannot be changed.

263
00:31:12,440 --> 00:31:14,959
But if one sincerely
turns toward good thoughts

264
00:31:14,960 --> 00:31:20,240
and good deeds, it is never too late.

265
00:31:21,200 --> 00:31:25,040
Your merit in this life is exhausted.

266
00:31:25,640 --> 00:31:28,399
You should let go of your desires

267
00:31:28,400 --> 00:31:31,960
and go to the realm where you belong.

268
00:31:32,640 --> 00:31:35,760
Why stubbornly remain
half-ghost, half-human,

269
00:31:36,360 --> 00:31:40,480
forcing your body to keep suffering?

270
00:31:41,280 --> 00:31:45,320
Don't preach to me.
Just mind your business.

271
00:32:38,560 --> 00:32:41,680
Mook, wake up.

272
00:32:42,400 --> 00:32:43,560
Mook.

273
00:32:48,440 --> 00:32:49,560
What is it?

274
00:32:50,320 --> 00:32:54,200
Na and I are going back. We're going
to stop by somewhere else on the way.

275
00:32:56,280 --> 00:32:57,119
Go ahead.

276
00:32:57,120 --> 00:32:59,480
Okay. See you in Bangkok.

277
00:33:17,600 --> 00:33:19,760
MR. NARATHON

278
00:33:23,680 --> 00:33:25,319
I must have waited until I fell asleep,

279
00:33:25,320 --> 00:33:28,360
then dreamed
that Mr. Narathon messaged me.

280
00:33:45,120 --> 00:33:48,919
Dear,
you keep bending up and down like that.

281
00:33:48,920 --> 00:33:50,960
Don't complain later when your back hurts.

282
00:33:51,480 --> 00:33:54,080
It's just a little exercise.

283
00:33:56,640 --> 00:33:59,519
Mook, you're awake?

284
00:33:59,520 --> 00:34:00,840
Yes, Mom.

285
00:34:03,160 --> 00:34:04,279
Did you sleep late last night?

286
00:34:04,280 --> 00:34:08,199
What were you doing?
I saw you go into your room early.

287
00:34:11,760 --> 00:34:14,119
We're heading back to Bangkok
later this morning.

288
00:34:14,120 --> 00:34:17,439
Go have breakfast first.
I prepared it for you.

289
00:34:17,440 --> 00:34:19,479
- Okay.
- I'll go pack your things for you.

290
00:34:19,480 --> 00:34:20,520
Okay.

291
00:34:28,440 --> 00:34:30,320
I'M WAITING FOR YOU AT THE BEACH.

292
00:34:32,880 --> 00:34:34,360
Who's messaging you this early?

293
00:34:36,679 --> 00:34:39,198
Oh, just a sales account.

294
00:34:39,199 --> 00:34:42,840
They send messages all day.
I should probably mute the notifications.

295
00:34:48,639 --> 00:34:49,679
Wait.

296
00:34:58,920 --> 00:35:00,320
Isn't this your scarf?

297
00:35:01,960 --> 00:35:04,080
Yes. Why?

298
00:35:06,160 --> 00:35:09,000
You dropped it in front of the house.
I went for a walk this morning

299
00:35:09,720 --> 00:35:10,760
and picked it up for you.

300
00:35:11,520 --> 00:35:12,640
Thank you.

301
00:35:25,240 --> 00:35:26,640
Mr. Narathon.

302
00:35:31,480 --> 00:35:34,679
I saw your message,
that you wanted to see me and Da.

303
00:35:34,680 --> 00:35:38,039
But Da went back to Bangkok with Na.
They were stopping somewhere on the way.

304
00:35:38,040 --> 00:35:39,040
I see.

305
00:35:40,560 --> 00:35:42,200
Is something wrong?

306
00:35:43,600 --> 00:35:47,520
I wanted to ask Ms. Da
for more details about that woman ghost.

307
00:35:48,920 --> 00:35:52,720
But it's all right.
We can arrange to meet again in Bangkok.

308
00:35:54,280 --> 00:35:56,640
You're going back to Bangkok today too?

309
00:35:57,320 --> 00:35:59,440
Yes. What about you?

310
00:36:00,040 --> 00:36:01,240
I'm going back today too.

311
00:36:06,920 --> 00:36:09,520
Then I should go.

312
00:36:11,480 --> 00:36:12,800
Wait.

313
00:36:20,320 --> 00:36:21,440
Excuse me.

314
00:36:54,280 --> 00:36:56,079
You know how to tie scarves?

315
00:36:56,080 --> 00:36:57,360
Yes.

316
00:36:58,280 --> 00:36:59,640
Someone taught me.

317
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:02,559
A woman, I bet.

318
00:37:02,560 --> 00:37:04,080
Yes.

319
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:09,000
Then, I'm leaving now.

320
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:11,520
Hey, wait.

321
00:37:15,760 --> 00:37:19,200
Why are you suddenly
using that tone with me?

322
00:37:20,360 --> 00:37:21,360
What tone?

323
00:37:23,440 --> 00:37:25,040
Before you misunderstand anything,

324
00:37:26,080 --> 00:37:28,760
the woman who taught me
was a 60-year-old foreign lady.

325
00:37:29,360 --> 00:37:32,480
She was the family I stayed with
when I studied abroad.

326
00:37:34,280 --> 00:37:36,919
When I lived abroad,

327
00:37:36,920 --> 00:37:39,920
it was different. it was very cold.

328
00:37:40,760 --> 00:37:42,879
It was necessary

329
00:37:42,880 --> 00:37:46,000
to use scarves. So I learned it from her.

330
00:37:46,760 --> 00:37:48,680
You didn't have to explain that much.

331
00:37:51,960 --> 00:37:53,680
I don't want you to misunderstand me.

332
00:37:57,840 --> 00:37:59,080
I was just kidding.

333
00:38:07,760 --> 00:38:08,840
What's wrong?

334
00:38:12,400 --> 00:38:14,960
I thought

335
00:38:16,400 --> 00:38:17,680
you were jealous of me.

336
00:38:21,040 --> 00:38:22,800
Well, I'm sorry.

337
00:38:23,840 --> 00:38:25,080
You should go back inside.

338
00:38:39,480 --> 00:38:44,120
If you ever do anything suspicious,
I'll definitely deal with you.

339
00:38:51,840 --> 00:38:54,320
I'm going now.

340
00:39:21,840 --> 00:39:23,400
I'm feeling better now.

341
00:39:25,000 --> 00:39:26,960
I finished all my breakfast this morning.

342
00:39:28,920 --> 00:39:29,960
That's good.

343
00:39:30,840 --> 00:39:33,479
Can I leave the hospital now?

344
00:39:33,480 --> 00:39:36,560
If the doctor approves,
there shouldn't be any problem.

345
00:39:38,120 --> 00:39:40,080
You'll take me with you, won't you?

346
00:39:43,080 --> 00:39:46,000
I won't trouble you for long. I promise.

347
00:39:46,640 --> 00:39:50,560
I can do housework. I can cook,

348
00:39:51,200 --> 00:39:53,520
do laundry, wash dishes.
I can do everything.

349
00:40:01,480 --> 00:40:02,960
You don't believe me?

350
00:40:05,720 --> 00:40:08,960
Well, when I first saw you,

351
00:40:09,480 --> 00:40:11,839
I thought you were a rich person.

352
00:40:11,840 --> 00:40:14,680
But the qualities
you just described sound like...

353
00:40:16,280 --> 00:40:17,520
Like who?

354
00:40:19,560 --> 00:40:21,920
- Like...
- So you've been holed up with this woman.

355
00:40:26,080 --> 00:40:26,920
Sairung?

356
00:40:35,760 --> 00:40:36,920
This is...

357
00:40:38,040 --> 00:40:39,120
You shameless woman!

358
00:40:40,120 --> 00:40:41,160
Stop.

359
00:40:43,840 --> 00:40:45,199
What are you doing, Sairung?

360
00:40:45,200 --> 00:40:47,599
Let go of me. I'm going to kill her.

361
00:40:47,600 --> 00:40:50,200
This shameless woman
dares to steal my husband!

362
00:40:54,760 --> 00:40:56,200
If you want to go crazy,
go do it somewhere else.

363
00:40:56,760 --> 00:40:59,480
Before I lose control
and hurt you worse than this.

364
00:41:03,760 --> 00:41:05,560
You dared to slap me?

365
00:41:39,320 --> 00:41:43,240
I'm sorry for what she did.
Are you alright?

366
00:41:46,320 --> 00:41:50,520
I should apologize to you instead.
I made her misunderstand you.

367
00:41:52,960 --> 00:41:56,320
Now I understand why you can't help me.

368
00:41:58,000 --> 00:41:59,920
I won't trouble you anymore.

369
00:42:02,000 --> 00:42:03,440
Don't say that.

370
00:42:07,960 --> 00:42:09,360
I'll take you with me.

371
00:42:13,280 --> 00:42:14,560
Really?

372
00:42:16,760 --> 00:42:19,040
I'll go settle the hospital bill first.

373
00:42:41,320 --> 00:42:42,720
Are you full now?

374
00:42:44,880 --> 00:42:46,880
It'll be several hours
before we reach Bangkok.

375
00:42:47,640 --> 00:42:48,920
I'm not very hungry.

376
00:42:50,880 --> 00:42:54,600
By the way, what should I call you?

377
00:42:59,600 --> 00:43:01,440
Could you give me a name?

378
00:43:02,840 --> 00:43:04,680
Name you?

379
00:43:06,160 --> 00:43:09,599
I found you by the sea.
It should be something related to

380
00:43:09,600 --> 00:43:11,920
the sea and coral.

381
00:43:13,840 --> 00:43:14,960
Pakarang?

382
00:43:16,760 --> 00:43:18,280
How about Pakarang?

383
00:43:18,880 --> 00:43:19,840
Pakarang?

384
00:43:25,240 --> 00:43:27,879
Sure, that sounds good. I love it.

385
00:43:27,880 --> 00:43:30,440
Then from now on, I'll call you Pakarang.

386
00:43:31,040 --> 00:43:32,240
Okay.

387
00:43:35,000 --> 00:43:36,600
I'm done eating.

388
00:43:37,640 --> 00:43:38,800
Bill, please.

389
00:44:11,880 --> 00:44:14,360
What happened? I'll go check.

390
00:44:16,600 --> 00:44:17,600
Mr. Phum.

391
00:44:18,520 --> 00:44:19,880
Wait in the car.

392
00:44:23,680 --> 00:44:24,520
Sir.

393
00:44:25,960 --> 00:44:27,280
Sir.

394
00:44:38,240 --> 00:44:39,960
What's going on?

395
00:44:40,640 --> 00:44:42,000
Hey, take her!

396
00:44:43,560 --> 00:44:44,639
Come here!

397
00:44:44,640 --> 00:44:45,560
‎Come.

398
00:44:46,400 --> 00:44:47,560
Let go of me!

399
00:44:53,280 --> 00:44:54,600
Where did Sarai disappear to?

400
00:45:03,520 --> 00:45:05,279
Mr. Thon, do you know this woman?

401
00:45:05,280 --> 00:45:08,440
A life must be paid for with a life.

402
00:45:09,800 --> 00:45:12,080
Sarai, don't.

403
00:45:13,920 --> 00:45:14,919
Sarai.

404
00:45:14,920 --> 00:45:16,519
<i>Who is Sarai?</i>

405
00:45:16,520 --> 00:45:19,600
Could you tell me about Sarai?

406
00:45:53,760 --> 00:45:55,640
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
